WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.200
So this is Posit Team. We're going to start up here at the top with the data scientists,

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:10.960
the data analysts, the folks that are actually writing code. And many times their job is to

00:00:10.960 --> 00:00:15.600
create insights and to share those insights. So let's start by going to the left here and

00:00:15.600 --> 00:00:22.080
creating insights. They're going to be writing code. They can use R, Python, they can use whatever

00:00:22.080 --> 00:00:29.280
IDE they want, either RStudio, JupyterLab, Jupyter Notebooks, VS Code, all within Posit Workbench.

00:00:29.760 --> 00:00:34.000
So Posit Workbench is our server-based implementation of the various IDEs.

00:00:34.959 --> 00:00:38.639
And your data scientists are writing code, again, in whatever language they want.

00:00:38.639 --> 00:00:42.720
So if you're within R, they might be creating things like Shiny applications,

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:48.560
pins, R Markdown, Plumber. But if they're Python developers, they might be creating things like

00:00:48.560 --> 00:00:53.840
Flask or FastAPI, Streamlit, Dash, Bokeh applications, Jupyter Notebooks.

00:00:54.560 --> 00:00:58.080
Maybe they're also creating Quarto documents, which is one of our newest tools.

00:00:59.439 --> 00:01:04.080
So when they create content like this, it doesn't do anyone any good if you can't share it with the

00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:09.599
people that need to see it. And that's the whole purpose of Posit Connect, our second tool within

00:01:09.599 --> 00:01:15.919
Posit Team. This is our professional publishing platform. And this makes it super easy to share

00:01:15.919 --> 00:01:21.040
all the cool content you see here with the people that need to see it, like your boss, decision

00:01:21.040 --> 00:01:26.639
makers, maybe yourself, maybe your friends or family. You can share it with Posit Connect.

00:01:27.599 --> 00:01:32.239
So for today's session, we're primarily going to live within Posit Workbench and Posit Connect.

00:01:32.239 --> 00:01:37.120
But there's also one other tool we'll touch upon today, and that's Posit Package Manager.

00:01:37.120 --> 00:01:42.959
And it does pretty much as its name implies. It helps control all those great open source

00:01:42.959 --> 00:01:50.400
packages within R and Python. Also, any packages you've created yourself within Workbench and

00:01:50.400 --> 00:01:55.839
Connect. And so we'll talk about all three of these tools today that, again, round out Posit Team.

00:01:56.639 --> 00:01:57.680
Thank you.

